00:39:27.370 --> 00:39:28.880
I think that's important.

00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:31.970
We've moved beyond the
days of burger and bud,

00:39:31.970 --> 00:39:37.299
and pork nachos and beer,
and all sorts of things.

00:39:37.299 --> 00:39:38.840
There's a lot of
great diversity that

00:39:38.840 --> 00:39:40.171
comes with food these days.

00:39:40.171 --> 00:39:41.670
And there's a lot
of great diversity

00:39:41.670 --> 00:39:43.910
that comes with beer these days.

00:39:43.910 --> 00:39:46.520
And really quickly,
I'll just say

00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:49.070
that it's been fun
to watch the way

00:39:49.070 --> 00:39:50.630
that the two worlds--
the food world

00:39:50.630 --> 00:39:55.341
and the beer world have evolved
together in the last few years.

00:39:55.341 --> 00:39:57.840
So we talked about prohibition,
and after prohibition how we

00:39:57.840 --> 00:40:00.200
all kind of became these
generic-- oh, yeah,

00:40:00.200 --> 00:40:03.830
I'll-- these generic beers that
were out there, these lagers.

00:40:03.830 --> 00:40:06.480
Our food culture kind of
went the same way as well.

00:40:06.480 --> 00:40:08.800
Our grandparents, our
great grandparents,

00:40:08.800 --> 00:40:11.260
they all knew where dinner
came from every night.

00:40:11.260 --> 00:40:15.340
And so you'd have fresh
baked bread on the table.

00:40:15.340 --> 00:40:18.010
Your meat came from
the local butcher.

00:40:18.010 --> 00:40:19.790
Your vegetables came
from the green grocer

00:40:19.790 --> 00:40:21.220
or from the backyard.

00:40:21.220 --> 00:40:23.075
And you knew what
it was that you

00:40:23.075 --> 00:40:24.310
were putting into your body.

00:40:24.310 --> 00:40:26.980
But slowly over
time, that changed

00:40:26.980 --> 00:40:29.640
and we became this culture of
convenience and mass-produced.

00:40:29.640 --> 00:40:32.620
And so real cheese
became Velveeta.

00:40:32.620 --> 00:40:35.070
And fresh-baked bread
became Wonder Bread.

00:40:35.070 --> 00:40:37.982
And rather than
working on a dinner,

00:40:37.982 --> 00:40:40.440
even if it would only take an
hour at the end of the night,

00:40:40.440 --> 00:40:42.620
we convinced ourselves
that we were so busy

00:40:42.620 --> 00:40:44.824
that we pop a plastic
tray into the microwave,

00:40:44.824 --> 00:40:46.490
and whatever came out
two minutes later,

00:40:46.490 --> 00:40:49.040
we'd call that dinner.

00:40:49.040 --> 00:40:50.040
We've moved on.

00:40:50.040 --> 00:40:52.130
I mean we still have a lot
of that in the country,

00:40:52.130 --> 00:40:55.020
but we're starting to see
more and more that people care

00:40:55.020 --> 00:40:56.640
about where their
food is coming from.

00:40:56.640 --> 00:40:58.500
They want to know
who's making their food

00:40:58.500 --> 00:41:00.570
The localvore movement
is coming back into play.

00:41:00.570 --> 00:41:03.199
Farmers' markets haven't
been this popular in ages.

00:41:03.199 --> 00:41:04.740
People really care
about what they're

00:41:04.740 --> 00:41:05.740
putting in their bodies.

00:41:05.740 --> 00:41:08.790
And the same thing is true
for the brewing industry.

00:41:08.790 --> 00:41:11.430
You can walk into your
local brewers around here--

00:41:11.430 --> 00:41:14.022
and you guys have quite a
few here in the LA area,

00:41:14.022 --> 00:41:15.730
and more and more it
seems all the time--

00:41:15.730 --> 00:41:18.180
and you can meet the
people who make your beer.

00:41:18.180 --> 00:41:22.350
You can shake the hand
of the guy or woman who

00:41:22.350 --> 00:41:24.240
made what is now in your glass.

00:41:24.240 --> 00:41:26.047
And that's a personal
connection, as well.

00:41:26.047 --> 00:41:28.130
It's like knowing where
your vegetables came from.

00:41:28.130 --> 00:41:30.370
And so to see the
craft beer movement

00:41:30.370 --> 00:41:32.860
and the localvore movement
kind of come together

00:41:32.860 --> 00:41:36.440
has really been great for
the beer and food movement,

00:41:36.440 --> 00:41:37.740
and books like this.

00:41:37.740 --> 00:41:39.590
So that's just another
thing to think about.

00:41:39.590 --> 00:41:41.610
When you're buying
craft beer, you're

00:41:41.610 --> 00:41:44.500
supporting smaller businesses,
you're supporting local,

00:41:44.500 --> 00:41:48.240
and you're doing your part
to do right by yourself

00:41:48.240 --> 00:41:52.330
by getting some good, flavorful
beer into your system.

